-- London Stock Exchange sees 50 pct rise in revenue
-- 
-- Thu May 15, 2014 02:13AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, May 15 (Reuters) - The London Stock Exchange <LSE.L> reported a 50 percent rise in full year reported revenue on Thursday, saying expansion in capital markets infrastructure had boosted profits.

The exchange group said revenue for the year ended March 31 was 1.09 billion pounds ($1.8 billion), up from 762.4 million pounds a year earlier and above analysts' expectations.